1
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:15,367
The patient is still in a coma.

2
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,833
We need to closely monitor
her vital signs

3
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:21,033
while we wait for the results
of her tests.

4
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:24,167
None of this would have happened
if you did not get in our way!

5
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:25,367
You're a fake doctor!

6
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:26,767
And now, a fake mom, too!

7
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,100
That's nonsense!

8
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:30,767
Now you can operate on
that long horn of yours!

9
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:32,700
Our daughter!

10
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,267
Doctor! Nurse!

11
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,667
Olive, you kidnapped Mookie!

12
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:38,267
And if they find solid evidence,

13
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,233
they might open up what you did
on Danilo!

14
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,200
They can file multiple cases
against you!

15
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:45,133
They said his testimony wasn't
strong enough

16
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,967
to file a case against Olive.

17
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:48,867
I do not have anything to prove.

18
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:51,133
I have the right to refuse
the DNA test,

19
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,567
especially now that the child is
still in a critical condition.

20
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,167
Don't you want to know
the truth?

21
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:31,467
So there you have it, friends.

22
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:34,067
We are currently here
at the Ladera Medical Center.

23
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:35,233
And I personally heard it!

24
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,100
I heard that Emma Joseco dared
Olive Caparas

25
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:41,200
to undergo a DNA test.

26
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,533
Right, friends?
Most of you asked for this!

27
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,633
So let's go and see what's
happening.

28
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:48,700
Are you afraid that the truth
will come out?

29
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,400
Of course not!

30
00:01:50,467 --> 00:01:53,167
I just think this stint
is too cheap!

31
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:55,367
Excuse me?

32
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:56,133
I know her.

33
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,100
Excuse me...

34
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:01,933
We can actually help you with
your decision.

35
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:04,133
Who are you?

36
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:07,200
It's you again?

37
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:08,467
I am Maricon.

38
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:10,767
I am a vlogger, podcaster.

39
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:12,133
I have a lot of followers.

40
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,900
And my subscribers
have a suggestion.

41
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,267
We hope you can grant their
request.

42
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:19,533
And what is it?

43
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:36,100
See, Miss Olive, Miss Emma...

44
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:37,567
you have lots of fans.

45
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:38,867
Look at this.

46
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:41,567
Hashtag Team Olive, press one.

47
00:02:41,633 --> 00:02:43,067
See, that's a lot.

48
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:45,967
Hashtag Team Emma, press two.

49
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:51,433
That's a lot, too.
They're all online.

50
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,300
Look at this comment.

51
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:57,000
Maybe you do not want a DNA test

52
00:02:57,067 --> 00:03:01,867
because you are scared
that the public will find out

53
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:04,467
the truth about the kidnapping
that you did on Miss Emma's kid.

54
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:06,400
Yes, that's correct.

55
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:07,533
Of course not!

56
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,233
Oh, that is absolutely true!

57
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:12,133
Miss Olive is a kidnapper!

58
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,000
That is not true!

59
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:16,467
Well then, prove it.

60
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:18,833
Have a DNA test.

61
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:21,433
If you do not want to do
the DNA test,

62
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:22,967
that only means one thing...

63
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,200
What they're saying is true!

64
00:03:26,267 --> 00:03:27,367
No!

65
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,467
Fine!

66
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,567
I will agree to that woman's
plea.

67
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,467
I will agree to do the DNA test.

68
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,433
But on one condition...

69
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:47,233
We will do a specialized
DNA test.

70
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:58,433
I actually do not want
to agree to the vlogger

71
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,667
because I do not want my child
to be everyone's topic again.

72
00:04:12,933 --> 00:04:18,133
You are the only person
who took care of me like this.

73
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:22,233
I want you to become my mother.

74
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:25,800
I believe that you will get
better and go back to normal.

75
00:04:25,867 --> 00:04:31,733
You are the only person who told
me I still have a chance

76
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:33,133
to get better.

77
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:37,333
You know what, Mom, I really
feel like I am your daughter.

78
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:41,967
I feel like you are my mother.

79
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:44,800
Thank you, Mommy Emma.

80
00:04:55,033 --> 00:04:59,333
I pushed Olive to do it.

81
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,933
Good thing she agreed.

82
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,767
She cannot say no to me.

83
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:03,667
Right?

84
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,000
It's because I'm beautiful.

85
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:12,500
Dear, stop frowning!
That's enough.

86
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,967
Danilo's there, and also Bukoy.

87
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,800
They are still talking
to the police.

88
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:18,333
The truth will come out.

89
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:21,200
Now, smile a little.

90
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:31,400
But Mom, that's the only
way for Olive to agree.

91
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:38,333
What's important to me now
is Mookie's recovery.

92
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:41,700
I want to talk to her again.

93
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:46,767
I want to see her smile again,
Mom.

94
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:51,367
I like it when she calls me
"Mommy".

95
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,733
Everybody wants that!

96
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,767
I also felt that way when
she called me "Grandmother".

97
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,800
It felt so good to be called
Grandmother.

98
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:11,333
I just thought, when she
was younger,

99
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,100
I wanted her to get adopted.

100
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:16,700
I met a wealthy couple.

101
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:20,567
They are willing to pay for the
hospitalization of Baby Kayla.

102
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:21,767
Really?

103
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:25,700
They will pay for everything
until she grows up.

104
00:06:26,933 --> 00:06:29,733
If you would agree
with the adoption.

105
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:35,867
I wanted to punish myself!

106
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:40,733
Could you imagine I did that?

107
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,800
I was a bad grandmother.

108
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:48,700
Mom, stop thinking about it.

109
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:50,967
How can I stop thinking about
that?

110
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:53,100
Imagine?

111
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:56,733
I know how it feels
to lose a child...

112
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,100
Yet I suggested that you
give her up for adoption?

113
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:02,500
I did not even consider
how you would feel?

114
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:05,467
I was so mean, right?

115
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:08,867
I am sorry.

116
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:12,533
I am very sorry.

117
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:21,633
But when we were having
a good time with Mookie,

118
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:25,000
I realized that it feels good
to have people around.

119
00:07:25,067 --> 00:07:26,933
It feels so good to have
a grandchild.

120
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:34,667
I thought if I did not
have your siblings adopted,

121
00:07:34,733 --> 00:07:36,667
we would have been happier.

122
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:38,900
Right?

123
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,033
Mom...

124
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,100
I am sorry.

125
00:07:51,933 --> 00:07:53,567
I am very sorry.

126
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:09,433
I cannot convince my friend
to consult with you.

127
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:15,000
But lately, I feel like it's
more than Munchausen by Proxy.

128
00:08:15,067 --> 00:08:16,467
What do you mean?

129
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:21,500
She adopted a child when her
daughter died in an accident.

130
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,367
And now she's saying she's
the biological mother

131
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:25,933
and that she gave birth to her.

132
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,833
She may be experiencing DMS

133
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:33,100
or Delusional Misidentification
Syndrome.

134
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:36,367
Delusional Misidentification
Syndrome

135
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:40,067
is the various delusions
of a person

136
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:44,367
who misidentifies individuals,
objects, or places.

137
00:08:44,433 --> 00:08:46,567
In the case of your friend,

138
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:50,400
she has this delusion that she
genuinely believes

139
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:53,867
that her adoptive daughter
is her real daughter.

140
00:08:56,767 --> 00:08:58,000
Maria Angela!

141
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:00,567
My daughter!

142
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,200
Your life is in danger here.

143
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:08,833
They're going to collect
your DNA samples.

144
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,333
And Emma will just rig
the results

145
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,100
to take you away from me!

146
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:16,700
No!

147
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,633
I will not let that happen!

148
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:27,133
I have to take you away
from here!

149
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,900
What are you going to do with
my daughter?

150
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:15,633
Are you going to abduct her
again?

151
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,133
Are you going to take her?

152
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,567
Or are you going to kill her?

153
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:22,900
What?

154
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:31,933
Until you find a solid evidence

155
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,900
that you are Mookie's
real mother,

156
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,133
I am still her mother!

157
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,600
I have the right as her mother!

158
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:46,167
So when I say you cannot visit
her, you will do as I say!

159
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,233
Get out!

160
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:54,067
Even if I have to stay here
inside the ICU for 24 hours,

161
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:55,400
I will do it!

162
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:57,667
Just to make sure that you
cannot take away my daughter!

163
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:03,567
And I will make sure that your
plans will never push through!

164
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:07,667
Nurse!

165
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,733
Nurse! Someone got in without
wearing a lab gown.

166
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:12,200
Ma'am, you are not allowed

167
00:11:12,267 --> 00:11:14,333
to go inside without wearing
sterile clothes.

168
00:11:17,433 --> 00:11:19,433
Let's go out now.

169
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:44,367
Delusional disorders are serious
mental health conditions,

170
00:11:44,467 --> 00:11:47,567
and they often require treatment
and support,

171
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:50,833
especially since your friend
is also diagnosed with MSBP.

172
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:54,033
You have to take her to me,
Astrid.

173
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:57,633
Before she even does something
that will affect some people.

174
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,667
There you have it, friends.

175
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:04,900
We heard about the DNA test
to prove who Mookie's mother is.

176
00:12:04,967 --> 00:12:07,367
And it is happening here right
now.

177
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:08,633
But the question remains...

178
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:12,033
Who is the biological mother
of Mookie?

179
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:14,067
Is it Team Olive or Team Emma?

180
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,233
This is getting exciting!

181
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:24,200
You know what, Emma?

182
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,467
You look so tired.

183
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,933
You look awful.

184
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:35,000
Maybe it's because you are
so tired of fighting

185
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:36,367
for this thing.

186
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:42,467
So if I were you, just rest...

187
00:12:43,967 --> 00:12:47,767
Six feet down under.

188
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:50,367
Don't worry.

189
00:12:51,467 --> 00:12:58,200
I will send your memorial plan
as a consolation prize.

190
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:01,633
When you took Mookie
away from me,

191
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:04,700
I thought my life was over.

192
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:07,633
But I stood up and fought
for her.

193
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:09,800
Why would I give up now?

194
00:13:09,867 --> 00:13:14,167
Now that it will be revealed
that I am Mookie's real mother?

195
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:16,467
That memorial plan is yours!

196
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:20,867
You might need it more than I do
when the truth comes out.

197
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,633
Poor you.

198
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:33,833
You are so hopeful that
you are Mookie's mother.

199
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:36,867
When the DNA results are out,

200
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:44,467
you might want to bury your own
body out of pure shame!

201
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,933
How I pity you.

202
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:53,133
Because the results will show
that I am Mookie's real mother.

203
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,567
Because that's the truth.

204
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:57,133
And you?

205
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,467
You will rot in prison!

206
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:01,767
Or in the asylum!

207
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:05,233
Not even your friends
can defend you.

208
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,000
You will rot alone.

209
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,900
You will die of loneliness...

210
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:13,867
More than how I felt when you
stole my daughter!

211
00:14:29,767 --> 00:14:33,267
It's a good thing that your
cousin is our pharmacist.

212
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:35,400
Yes, Ma'am.

213
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:39,500
You can do this fast
because you work here.

214
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:42,033
When the DNA test result comes
out,

215
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:45,167
I will give you additional pay.

216
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:50,633
Thank you, Ma'am.

217
00:14:58,133 --> 00:14:59,033
Hi, dear.

218
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,067
It's hard to come in here.

219
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,433
I have to wear all these.

220
00:15:06,633 --> 00:15:08,267
No one's here anyway.

221
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,567
Maybe I can put this down.

222
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:12,700
Hey!

223
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:15,367
I am talking to you.

224
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,367
Dear,

225
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,467
I am sorry.

226
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:25,033
When you were still a baby,

227
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,267
I planned to get you adopted.

228
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:31,933
You were so sickly.

229
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Sorry.

230
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,767
And when you'd grown,

231
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:41,400
I didn't want you to stay in
our house.

232
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:43,367
I hope you will not take this
against me.

233
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,600
Promise, I will make it up
to you.

234
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:49,767
You are so beautiful.

235
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,900
You know what? I have a plan.

236
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:04,333
I was thinking of how
I'd like you to call me.

237
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:10,600
I don't want to be called
granny. I feel so old!

238
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:14,867
You know me, I am groovy!

239
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:20,233
What do you think?

240
00:16:23,967 --> 00:16:30,800
Can you think of a better term
of endearment for me?

241
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:31,800
What do you think?

242
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,333
What will you call me?

243
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,933
Dear, I want to hear.

244
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,167
Come on.

245
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:47,600
Wake up.

246
00:16:47,667 --> 00:16:50,467
I want to hear what you will
call me.

247
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:56,500
She will wake up now.

248
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:59,733
Dear, wake up.

249
00:17:03,867 --> 00:17:05,967
Come on now.

250
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:19,200
Emma's really getting on
my nerves.

251
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:26,833
She acts as if she is very sure
their DNA test results

252
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:29,033
will match.

253
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:33,400
I have talked to someone
from the DNA testing center.

254
00:17:33,467 --> 00:17:36,600
She is a relative of one of our
pharmacists.

255
00:17:36,667 --> 00:17:38,500
I told her what to do.

256
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:54,800
And I'm pretty sure your DNA
will match with Mookie's.

257
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:09,533
Dear,

258
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:17,133
the doctor said you're
recovering.

259
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:25,033
When you wake up, you will be
transferred to a regular room.

260
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:34,300
Darling, wake up now.

261
00:18:49,467 --> 00:18:53,167
Do you remember this book?

262
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:59,233
When you wake up, we will
read this together, okay?

263
00:19:00,667 --> 00:19:02,667
Don't worry.

264
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:04,867
You will not be afraid.

265
00:19:05,967 --> 00:19:08,300
Because your real mother
is here.

266
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:11,767
I am here now, my dear.

267
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,567
Emma, Mom...

268
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:19,833
Someone from the DNA center
called.

269
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:21,967
They already have the result.

270
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:25,100
Let's go.

271
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:26,133
Let's go!

272
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,267
Dear, I will come back.

273
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:55,633
Mookie, you're gonna love this
doll that I bought for you.

274
00:19:57,367 --> 00:20:01,400
Olive, the DNA test result
is out.

275
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:09,067
Brace yourself, Emma.

276
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:13,467
Mookie will come back to me.

277
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:15,433
And we will have a happy

278
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,233
mother-daughter relationship
again.

279
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:37,400
So here it is!

280
00:20:37,467 --> 00:20:39,567
Guess what?

281
00:20:39,633 --> 00:20:47,833
I heard that the DNA test
result will be out soon!

282
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:49,867
Oh, my god!

283
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:54,333
So friends, stand by and see!

284
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,167
This is the DNA test result.

285
00:21:03,567 --> 00:21:04,700
Miss Caparas.

286
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:48,233
The DNA test result confirms

287
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:54,367
that Miss Emma Joseco is the
child's biological mother.

288
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:59,167
Maria Angela Caparas
is your daughter.

289
00:22:05,667 --> 00:22:08,667
- Mookie is our daughter!
- Dan, Mookie is Kayla!

290
00:22:10,733 --> 00:22:11,633
No!

291
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:18,733
- Mookie is our daughter! Yes!
- Dan, Mookie is Kayla!

292
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,133
No!

293
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,033
That test result is fake!

294
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,767
Miss Caparas, please calm down.

295
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,233
- The results are true.
- No!

296
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:48,867
No! You are trying to fool me!

297
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:54,500
You manipulated
the test results!

298
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,067
This is tampered with!

299
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:57,600
You are a monster!

300
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,767
Stop it, Olive!

301
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:02,400
If something bad happens
to my wife,

302
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:03,833
you will answer to me!

303
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:18,000
Doc, the patient is waking up!

304
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:20,400
I do not believe this!

305
00:23:20,467 --> 00:23:22,267
This is a fake test result!

306
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,933
This is tampered!
This is manipulated!

307
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,900
You are all allies!

308
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:27,833
What now?

309
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:30,633
Tell me!

310
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,500
Wow, Olive!

311
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,767
Do not put this on us!

312
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:37,600
You are a kidnapper!

313
00:23:37,667 --> 00:23:38,600
No!

314
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,633
You are allies with
this testing center!

315
00:23:41,667 --> 00:23:42,867
We do not have many resources

316
00:23:42,933 --> 00:23:45,900
to manipulate things like how
you do it!

317
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:48,667
That's the result
because it is the truth!

318
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:50,733
Mookie is my daughter!

319
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,400
And you kidnapped her!

320
00:23:52,467 --> 00:23:54,033
And now that the truth is out,

321
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:56,700
you will have to pay for
everything you did

322
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,000
to me and her!

323
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:02,633
Nurse, please inform the family.

324
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:04,833
I will take this to the court!

325
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:07,533
This testing center
will be closed!

326
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,367
You are all liars!

327
00:24:09,433 --> 00:24:10,500
Olive.

328
00:24:10,567 --> 00:24:11,600
Olive, let's go!

329
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:14,067
You will pay for this!

330
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:15,533
This is not the end!

331
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,667
No!

332
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:18,500
Olive, let's leave, let's go!

333
00:24:40,867 --> 00:24:42,533
Mookie is my grandchild!

334
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:50,833
What?

335
00:24:50,900 --> 00:24:53,200
Listen to me!

336
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:55,033
I talked to Myla.

337
00:24:57,267 --> 00:25:02,667
She felt guilty, so she did not
switch the specimen.

338
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:05,433
She transferred the money back
to me.

339
00:25:05,500 --> 00:25:07,333
What?

340
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,633
We have a huge problem.

341
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:13,200
Emma now has concrete proof
that Mookie is their daughter.

342
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:16,167
So, at any moment,
the police may arrest you.

343
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:17,033
No!
No!

344
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:20,233
This can't be!

345
00:25:21,267 --> 00:25:22,267
No!

346
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:23,767
I will not allow it!

347
00:25:25,567 --> 00:25:27,433
They can never take Mookie
away from me!

348
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:31,667
Emma now has concrete proof
that Mookie is their daughter.

349
00:25:31,733 --> 00:25:34,300
So, at any moment,
the police may arrest you.

350
00:25:34,367 --> 00:25:35,500
No!

351
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:36,133
No!

352
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,467
This can't be!

353
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:40,767
No!

354
00:25:40,833 --> 00:25:42,367
I will not allow it!

355
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:46,167
They can never take Mookie
away from me!

356
00:25:48,967 --> 00:25:52,367
Emma, I will just get the car.

357
00:25:52,433 --> 00:25:53,767
Wait for me.

358
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:57,900
I will call Kutsy and Wiro.
I will tell them the news.

359
00:25:57,967 --> 00:25:59,767
Oh, where is my phone?

360
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:01,800
- Emma, hold on.
- Okay, Mom.

361
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,067
Buy some, Ma'am.

362
00:26:07,567 --> 00:26:09,133
That's 20 pesos each.

363
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:12,133
Here it is, friends!

364
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:15,000
Emma Joseco won!

365
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,400
You are an animal!

366
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,167
This one's for you!

367
00:26:22,233 --> 00:26:23,400
What?

368
00:26:23,467 --> 00:26:26,433
Olive!

369
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,867
Stop that!

370
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,833
If you think this is the end,
you're wrong!

371
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:33,933
I will fight!

372
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:35,533
Stop it!

373
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,967
I will never stop!

374
00:26:39,033 --> 00:26:43,100
If you think you've already won,
Emma, you are wrong!

375
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:45,167
Oh, so you're still here?

376
00:26:45,233 --> 00:26:49,367
I thought you were getting your
defense statements ready!

377
00:26:49,433 --> 00:26:52,100
I have great lawyers
who can handle that.

378
00:26:52,167 --> 00:26:53,567
I have money!

379
00:26:53,633 --> 00:26:55,367
I have businesses!

380
00:26:55,433 --> 00:27:02,633
Maybe you can't even afford
medicine if Mookie becomes sick!

381
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:04,800
I will not let her take meds

382
00:27:04,867 --> 00:27:06,767
because I do not have
a mental illness like you!

383
00:27:08,433 --> 00:27:10,433
How dare you touch me!

384
00:27:11,733 --> 00:27:14,333
Are you looking for
a mental illness?

385
00:27:29,267 --> 00:27:31,333
You are safe from danger now.

386
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:34,933
I am Mookie's mother,
and I will not back down!

387
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:39,500
The DNA test result is strong
evidence against Miss Caparas.

388
00:27:39,567 --> 00:27:42,400
We can now prepare
a warrant of arrest.

389
00:27:42,467 --> 00:27:46,100
I will also testify on
Ma'am Olive's abuse of Mookie.

390
00:27:46,167 --> 00:27:49,700
Olive, stop with these
delusions!

391
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:52,200
Maria Angela has been dead
for a long time!

392
00:27:52,267 --> 00:27:54,167
She's facing multiple cases.

393
00:27:54,233 --> 00:27:55,733
I know that woman!

394
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:58,900
She will find a way to take
Mookie away from us!

395
00:27:58,967 --> 00:28:00,067
Hello?

396
00:28:00,133 --> 00:28:01,300
We're looking for Miss Caparas.

397
00:28:02,533 --> 00:28:04,067
This is the police!

398
00:28:04,133 --> 00:28:05,367
Oh my God, Olive!

399
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:07,167
They might arrest you!
